i asked aroudn a few people for some ideas of what we could do for user accounts

1. favorite commanders, basically just pin commanders you play a lot. then a few features can grow out of this. 1. we could email you when a new set comes out about which cards are seeing play for those commanders; 2. make it easier to see which commanders you have favorited in some sort of menu somewhere, like a bookmark; 3. show it in a public profile to show off what kinds of commanders you like to others; 4. some sort of matchmaking/recommendation engine for other commanders you might like; 5. favorite counter on commanders -- ie, top 50 most favorited commander of all time on the site
2. search history. basically a way to quickly go back to other pages you've looked at recently quickly. not sure the best place to put this without taking up much room though

3. archidekt/other site account linking. You give it your archidekt account name and it simply links to it, slurps your decks in and tags them with your username. will let you see the last time the deck has been picked up by edhrec. refresh button that tells edhrec to go fetch your deck and ingest it and check to see if there are any updates for it. When the deck is visible or in the list of decks, maybe make it bold and show the user name next to it. Help people get more visibility for their decks that they've associated with. people love this shit
4. pay to turn off ads
